# Agent Instructions

This project is an ASP.NET Minimal API sample using Dapr pub/sub with the in-memory component.

## Project overview

- Framework: .NET 10
- App type: ASP.NET Core Minimal API
- Dapr package: `Dapr.AspNetCore`
- Pub/sub component: `pubsub`
- Topic: `messages`

## Important files

- `src/Program.cs` - defines the Minimal API endpoints and Dapr subscription.
- `local/dapr-components/pubsub.yaml` - configures the Dapr in-memory pub/sub component.
- `src/{{ .name }}.http` - contains sample HTTP requests.
- `README.md` - contains run instructions.

## Development notes

- Keep the API minimal and focused on the Dapr pub/sub flow.
- Use `DaprClient.PublishEventAsync` to publish messages.
- Use `.WithTopic("pubsub", "messages")` for subscribed endpoints.
- Keep component names in sync between `src/Program.cs` and `local/dapr-components/pubsub.yaml`.

## Build and run

Build:

```bash
dotnet build ./src
```

Run with Dapr:

```bash
dapr run \
  --app-id {{ .appId }} \
  --app-port 5000 \
  --dapr-http-port 3500 \
  --resources-path ./local/dapr-components \
  -- dotnet run --project ./src --urls http://localhost:5000
```

## Testing

Use `src/{{ .name }}.http` to post a sample message to `POST /publish`.
